          "body": "Orthodox commentators agree on the chapter’s Christological core but divide on the relationship of the New Covenant to ethnic Israel. **Covenantal/Reformed** readings (Calvin, Owen, Hughes) hold that the church is the true Israel, and the New Covenant is fulfilled in the present church without remainder — the *house of Israel and Judah* of v. 8 are read inclusively. **Dispensational/progressive** readings (Pentecost, Hodges) hold that the church participates in the New Covenant’s soteriological blessings now, while its full national-territorial application to ethnic Israel awaits the millennial kingdom (Romans 11:25-27; Ezekiel 36-37). Both readings affirm Christ as mediator, the cross as the once-for-all sacrifice, and the present forgiveness of believers. The exegete should note the tension and resist collapsing it prematurely."
